title.div: The Gorseinion College Further Education Corporation and Swansea College Further Education Corporation (Dissolution) Order 2010 / Gorchymyn Corfforaeth Addysg Bellach Coleg Gorseinion a Chorfforaeth Addysg Bellach Coleg Abertawe (Diddymu) 2010

div.p: This Order dissolves the further education corporations established to conduct Gorseinion College (“Coleg Gorseinion”) and Swansea College (“Coleg Abertawe”) with effect from 20 August 2010. It provides for the transfer of the property, rights and liabilities of each corporation to Gower College Swansea Further Education Corporation (“Corfforaeth Addysg Bellach Coleg Gŵyr Abertawe”) and secures the employment rights of the employees of the dissolved corporations by applying section 26(2) to (4) of the Further and Higher Education Act 1992.

Mae'r Gorchymyn hwn yn diddymu'r corfforaethau addysg bellach a sefydlwyd i redeg Coleg Gorseinion (“Gorseinion College”) a Choleg Abertawe (“Swansea College”) a bydd y diddymu hwnnw yn cael ei effaith o 20 Awst 2010 ymlaen. Mae'n darparu ar gyfer trosglwyddo eiddo, hawliau a rhwymedigaethau'r naill gorfforaeth a'r llall i Gorfforaeth Addysg Bellach Coleg Gŵyr Abertawe (“Gower College Swansea Further Education Corporation”) ac yn sicrhau hawliau cyflogaeth cyflogeion y corfforaethau a ddiddymwyd drwy gymhwyso adran 26(2) i (4) o Ddeddf Addysg Bellach ac Uwch 1992.

title.div: The Zoonoses and Animal By-Products (Fees) (Wales) (Amendment) Regulations 2010 / Rheoliadau Milheintiau a Sgil-gynhyrchion Anifeiliaid (Ffioedd) (Cymru) (Diwygio) 2010

div.p: These Regulations, which apply in relation to Wales, amend the Zoonoses and Animal By-Products (Fees) (Wales) Regulations 2008 (S.I. 2008/2716) (W. 245). They make provision for the Welsh Ministers to charge fees for taking or supervising the taking of official samples and conducting testing required under Commission Regulation (EC) No 584/2008 (OJ No L 162, 21.6.2008, p. 3).

Mae'r Rheoliadau hyn, sy'n gymwys o ran Cymru, yn diwygio Rheoliadau Milheintiau a Sgilgyn-hyrchion Anifeiliaid (Ffioedd) (Cymru) 2008 (O.S. 2008/2716) (Cy. 245). Maent yn gwneud darpariaeth i Weinidogion Cymru godi ffioedd am gymryd samplau swyddogol, neu am oruchwylio'r broses o'u cymryd, ac am gynnal profion sy'n ofynnol o dan Reoliad y Comisiwn (EC) Rhif 584/2008 (OJ Rhif L 162, 21.6.2008, t. 3).

title.div: The Nutrition and Health Claims (Wales) (Amendment) Regulations 2010 / Rheoliadau Honiadau am Faethiad ac Iechyd (Cymru) (Diwygio) 2010

div.p: These Regulations amend the definition of “the Regulation”, meaning Regulation (EC) No. 1924/2006 of the European Parliament and of the Council on nutrition and health claims made on foods (OJ No. L12, 18.1.2007, p.3), contained in regulation 2 of the Nutrition and Health Claims (Wales) Regulations 2007 (S.I. 2007/2611). The effect of the amendment is that a reference to the Regulation in S.I. 2007/2611 now includes any future amendments to its Annex, which consists of the list of authorised nutrition claims and conditions relating to their use (regulation 3).

Mae'r Rheoliadau hyn yn diwygio'r diffiniad o “y Rheoliad”, sef Rheoliad (EC) Rhif 1924/2006 Senedd Ewrop a'r Cyngor ar honiadau am faethiad ac iechyd a wneir ar fwydydd (OJ Rhif L12, 18.1.2007, t.3), a geir yn rheoliad 2 o'r Rheoliadau Honiadau am Faethiad ac Iechyd (Cymru) 2007 (O.S. 2007/2611). Effaith y diwygiad yw bod cyfeiriad at y Rheoliad yn O.S. 2007/2611 bellach yn cynnwys unrhyw ddiwygiadau a wneir yn y dyfodol i'w Atodiad, sy'n cynnwys y rhestr o honiadau a awdurdodir am faethiad ac amodau sy'n ymwneud â'u defnyddio (rheoliad 3).

entry.title: The Stamp Duty and Stamp Duty Reserve Tax (Investment Exchanges and Clearing Houses) (Over the Counter) Regulations 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations exempt from stamp duty and stamp duty reserve tax (“SDRT”) certain transfers of, or agreements to transfer, traded securities made in the course of trading in those securities over the counter. Over the counter transactions are those that may have been made by two persons directly (whether or not through brokers) or arranged on behalf of the buyer and seller of the traded securities (whether or not on an anonymous basis). An over the counter transaction will not have been made on a recognised investment exchange and will not have been made in accordance with the rules of any recognised investment exchange.
